Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Job Title: Mid-Level AI Analyst - Governance & Ethics
Location: Sydney CBD
Employment Type: Full-time / long term contract opportunity
Salary: Negotiable contract rate on offer

About the Role

We are seeking a hands-on Mid-Level AI Analyst, and this role is ideal for someone passionate about AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks, who enjoys translating complex technical risks into practical advice and solutions.
You will work across government, enterprise, and technical teams to assess AI initiatives, monitor compliance, and support the implementation of robust governance processes. This is not a policy-making role , it's analytical, advisory, and deeply hands-on, offering exposure to cutting-edge AI projects in a high-impact environment.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct AI governance and ethics assessments across projects, identifying potential risks, bias, fairness, and compliance issues.
Support implementation of AI governance frameworks, approval gates, and monitoring processes.
Collaborate with policy, IT, legal, privacy, and business teams to provide clear, actionable guidance on AI projects.
Document and report findings, including risk assessments, dashboards, and governance committee materials.
Stay up to date with AI regulatory requirements, privacy laws, and ethical AI principles, ensuring projects align with best practice.
Assist in embedding responsible AI practices and frameworks.


Skills & Experience
Essential:

Hands-on experience in AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks.
Understanding of ethical AI principles: bias/fairness, & transparency.
Experience assessing AI projects for compliance, risk, and governance concerns.
Strong analytical skills and ability to review data sets, model outputs, or AI tools.
Experience with ServiceNow or similar governance/tracking tools.
Excellent communication skills to translate technical risks into clear advice for senior management.


Desirable / Nice-to-Have:

Background in government/public sector, consulting, finance, regulated industries, academia, or tech companies with AI governance exposure.
Knowledge of AI regulatory requirements, PIAs, or model risk frameworks.
Experience supporting governance committees, dashboards, and reporting frameworks.

"If AI governance and ethics excite you, we want to hear from you!"

How to Apply:
Please submit your CV and cover letter in Word format by clicking the "APPLY NOW" button below, or email your application to deqa.omer@talentinternational.com

Company: South Eastern Melbourne Primary Health Network
Ad Text:
About the role

As the Intelligence Automation Specialist, you will design and implement system-supported workflows and intelligent automation that improve efficiency, consistency, and scalability. You will translate governed business processes into reliable, explainable automation using low-code, rule-based, and selective AI-assisted approaches—ensuring strong controls, transparency, and human oversight.

Key responsibilities

Analyse end-to-end processes and identify automation opportunities

Design and implement workflows using low-code and rule-based platforms (e.g. Power Platform)

Build logic for validation, approvals, task routing, notifications, and exception handling

Configure event-driven, agent-assisted, and RPA solutions where appropriate

Ensure automation aligns with governance, privacy, security, and SOPs

Maintain documentation, version control, and change management

Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimise automation performance

Collaborate with Business Analysts, system support, governance, and IT teams


About you

Essential

Qualification in IT, Computer Science, or equivalent practical experience

Strong experience delivering workflow automation or low-code solutions

Ability to translate business rules into executable logic

Experience with validation, approvals, routing, and exception handling

Experience working across multiple systems in regulated environments

Strong documentation and communication skills

Experience with Microsoft Power Platform (e.g. Power Automate) or similar tools

Desirable

RPA or intelligent automation experience

Exposure to AI-assisted decision support in governed environments

Experience in health, government, or compliance-heavy sectors


Why You’ll Love It Here

Boost Your Take-Home Pay: Access generous salary packaging options

Flexible Work, Real Balance: Hybrid working that supports life outside work

Parental Leave That Cares: 10 weeks of paid parental leave

Extra Leave for You: Leave loading and dedicated festive leave

Support When It Matters: 5 additional paid carers leave days

Wellbeing First: Free, confidential EAP support for you and your family

Values-Led Culture: Purpose-driven, people-focused and genuinely collaborative

Health & Wellness: Access annual health programs, vaccinations and wellbeing initiatives

Grow With Us: Ongoing learning, development and career progression opportunities

Closing Date: 16 February 2026
